Hoechst AG's &lt;HFAG.F> U.S. unit,Hoechst Celanese Corp, said it has begun projects that willcost more than 150 mln dlrs.    The unit was formed last month when Hoechst completed theacquisition of Celanese for 2.84 billion dlrs.    The company said it will expand its Sanwet super absorbentpolymers unit and its acrylic acid facility. It also said itplans an acetaminophen production plant at Bishop, Texas. Reuter&#3;